            <title>[JDK-8302899] Executors.newSingleThreadExecutor can use Cleaner to shutdown executor</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8302899</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Executors.newSingleThreadExecutor returns a delegating ExecutorService with a finalize method to shutdown the underlying TPE. This was introduced via &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-6399443&quot; title=&quot;ThreadPoolExecutor leak&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-6399443&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-6399443&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in JDK 6. The finalizer can be trivially replaced with a Cleaner.</description>
